  "market_context": "Clear uptrend on EURUSD 5-minute chart; price had made an impulsive bullish move, then retraced toward a prior red candle defining a potential order block zone. Analyst emphasized waiting for pullback to enter longs.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed a double bottom at the order block zone on lower timeframe, then swept below equal lows (liquidity grab) before reversing strongly upward—classic SMC liquidity sweep setup.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the latest market structure as a clear uptrend, thus only considering buy opportunities.",
    "Step 2: Located the red candle preceding the impulsive bullish move as a potential order block (POI) for long entries.",
    "Step 3: Waited for price to retrace into that order block zone and zoomed into lower timeframe for confirmation.",
    "Step 4: Observed a double bottom reversal pattern at the zone, indicating failed bearish attempts and bearish weakness.",
    "Step 5: Noted that equal lows of the double bottom created a liquidity pool (SSL), anticipating a wick below to trigger stop-losses.",
    "Step 6: Recognized the subsequent wick below the equal lows as a bullish liquidity grab, confirming smart money entry before strong upward continuation."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In an uptrend, a double bottom at an order block signals potential reversal; a subsequent sweep below equal lows often serves as a liquidity grab before strong continuation—use this confluence for high-probability long entries.",
